<HEADLINE>
FT  30 SEP 92 / World News in Brief: Dublin seeks divorce vote
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
The Irish government proposed holding a referendum on the constitutional ban
on divorce. Divorce was rejected by an almost two-to-one majority in a
bitterly divisive referendum in 1986.
