<HEADLINE>
FT  30 SEP 92 / Observer: Servicing
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Liam Strong, chief executive of Sears, tells a story illustrating the
business of building customer loyalty.
A friend of his wanted to buy a car and looked at Toyota's Lexus. But he
bought a BMW. The Lexus sales manager called by and asked how the BMW was.
'Fine,' said the friend, 'except for the oddest thing; it came without an
ash-tray and I'm having the devil of a job finding one.'
Two days later a Lexus rep delivered a BMW ash-tray to the friend's house,
with a compliments slip from the sales manager.
</TEXT>
