FT  30 SEP 92 / C&amp;G cuts home loan rate by 1 point
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By DAVID BARCHARD
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
CHELTENHAM &amp; Gloucester, the sixth-largest building society, reduced its
mortgage interest rate yesterday by a full 1 percentage point to 9.75 per
cent (10.30 per cent APR), David Barchard writes.
Other large lenders, including Halifax and Abbey National, have cut their
standard rate by less than 1 percentage point to around 9.99 per cent since
the 1-point cut in the base rate to 9 per cent.
New customers will benefit immediately but Cheltenham &amp; Gloucester's cut
does not take effect for existing customers until December 1, a month later
than most other lenders.
TSB, the sixth-largest UK bank, has also cut its mortgage rate to 9.95 per
cent.
</TEXT>
