full-year earnings to be in line with those of the first half.
*****
Alitalia, Italy's flagship carrier, said that in spite of continuing
difficulties in the transport sector its first-half net loss narrowed to
L39bn (Dollars 32m) from L104bn in the same period last year, AP-DJ reports.
Revenue rose 22 per cent to L2,549bn.
*****
Saffa, the Italian paper and cardboard manufacturer, yesterday registered a
52 per cent fall in parent company pre-tax profits to L20.5bn for the first
half of 1992 from L42.8bn in the corresponding period of 1991.
