On the question of European Community quotas for the import of raw cane, Mr
Nicholas Nightingale, company secretary, said Tate &amp; Lyle expected a
decision 'in due course'. The temporary arrangement agreed when Portugal
joined the EC is due to end this year. 'We are sure we will end up with a
satisfactory basis,' he said.
Alcantara employs 570 people and has two refineries. Mr Nightingale said
there would be no management changes.
