<HEADLINE>
FT  29 SEP 92 / Management (The Growing Business): How vocational training
can pay - In A Nutshell
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Many people engaged in vocational training are not making use of tax breaks
which are available, according to the Inland Revenue.
UK residents who do not receive any other government assistance awards can
claim a discount on training towards National Vocational Qualifications and
their Scottish equivalent.
Trainees complete a form provided by the training organisation and deduct 25
per cent (the basic rate of tax) from their study, examination and
assessment fees.
Even non-taxpayers can get this discount while higher rate taxpayers can get
relief at the higher rate through their tax office.
