<TEXT>
'I am sure there are people here who take the view that the Labour party can
form the government after the next election.
I should tell you, though it may come as some surprise, that there were
people in Harrogate last week who thought the Liberal Democrats could form
the government after the next election.'
Menzies Campbell Liberal Democrat MP
'(Under Maastricht) any Labour chancellor might just as well hang a notice
on his door saying 'Gone on Holiday'.'
Diane Abbott
'Trades unions by and large don't like the dominant position they have at
the party conference. There is a lot of misunderstanding about this.'
John Edmonds, general secretary, GMB
'You let the Labour party loose on writing a new constitution and the year
2050 beckons fairly rapidly.'
Edmonds again
'I will try and grunt my way through the next 10 minutes.'
John Prescott, shadow transport secretary, addressing a fringe meeting
'The backdrop to this conference platform says everything. How many shades
of grey are there?'
Delegate during debate on election campaign
